You can use the pdfpages package in LaTeX to include multiple PDF files in a single document. Here is an example of how you can use this package to join two PDF files, file1.pdf and file2.pdf, into a single document:

\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{pdfpages}

\begin{document}
\includepdf[pages=-]{file1.pdf}
\includepdf[pages=-]{file2.pdf}
\end{document}
This will include all pages from file1.pdf followed by all pages from file2.pdf in the final document. You can also specify specific page ranges if you only want to include certain pages from each file. For example, to include only pages 1-3 from file1.pdf and pages 4-6 from file2.pdf, you would use the following code:

\includepdf[pages={1-3}]{file1.pdf}
\includepdf[pages={4-6}]{file2.pdf}
Please note that you will need to have pdflatex installed in your system to run this

